{"id": "EUVD-2026-2498", "enisaUuid": "f82e71df-7451-3b55-a0c5-19ab1feeb67c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/msm/a6xx: move preempt_prepare_postamble after error check\n\nMove the call to preempt_prepare_postamble() after verifying that\npreempt_postamble_ptr is valid. If preempt_postamble_ptr is NULL,\ndereferencing it in preempt_prepare_postamble() would lead to a crash.\n\nThis change avoids calling the preparation function when the\npostamble allocation has failed, preventing potential NULL pointer\ndereference and ensuring proper error handling.\n\nPatchwork: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/687659/", "datePublished": "2026-01-14T15:06:09", "dateUpdated": "2026-01-14T15:06:09", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-71124", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2c46497eb148ec61909f4101b8443f3c4c2daaec", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ef3b04091fd8bc737dc45312375df8625b8318e2"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-71124", "GHSA-9mpp-7gwm-7rx8"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0100d938-7862-3826-931f-81c148df889a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18.3"}, {"id": "0c8a529b-d2b3-3207-b88e-61502ee34905", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.13"}, {"id": "326a1446-5f1c-3066-81ef-334113d77ad7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "50117cad0c50410cff0d43a1141a562b1347e7c5 <ef3b04091fd8bc737dc45312375df8625b8318e2"}, {"id": "b345ba68-ff19-3250-9f0b-4f0fd793393c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "50117cad0c50410cff0d43a1141a562b1347e7c5 <2c46497eb148ec61909f4101b8443f3c4c2daaec"}, {"id": "bc74eb44-b884-3170-a7e7-e5227edd0f8b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "ff202165-13d9-3a00-9d08-358a08c41441", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.19-rc3"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "cb295941-12db-3ac5-9406-7aa63f609b72", "vendor": {"name": "